Yes, within 120 days of the enactment of the relevant subsection, the Commission is required to establish regulations to limit children's access to indecent programming. These actions include: 
(A) Requiring cable operators to place all indecent programs on a single channel; 
(B) Mandating cable operators block this single channel unless subscribers specifically request access in writing; 
(C) Programmers must inform cable operators if a program is considered indecent as per Commission regulations.

When awarding a franchise, a franchising authority may:
(A) Allow the applicant's cable system a reasonable time to provide cable service to all households in the franchise area;
(B) Require adequate assurance of sufficient public, educational, and governmental access channel capacity, facilities, or financial support;
(C) Require assurance that the cable operator has the necessary financial, technical, or legal qualifications to provide the service.

